Investor FAQs
 
Show all 

 How can I contact Dollar General's  transfer agent? 

	Wells Fargo Shareowner Services acts as the Transfer agent for shares of Dollar General stock. Inquiries regarding stock transfers, lost certificates or address changes should be directed to the transfer agent at:

	Wells Fargo Bank, NA, Shareowner Services, P.O. Box 64854, St. Paul, MN 55164-0854

	Web address: www.wellsfargo.com/shareownerservices Telephone: 800-468-9716

 I owned shares in Dollar General prior to July 6, 2007. Can I still redeem these for cash? 

	On July 6, 2007, all shares of Dollar General stock were acquired by private equity investors for $22.00 per share. If you still have not surrendered your stock certificates representing stock outstanding immediately prior to the merger or have not been paid for shares owned through the Dollar General Direct Stock Purchase and Dividend Reinvestment Plan, please direct your questions as soon as possible to the paying agent, Registrar & Transfer Company, at (800) 368-5948. If you held shares in a broker account, please contact your broker.

 Do you franchise your stores? 

	No, all Dollar General stores are company operated.

 Do you have another question that hasn't been answered?

Please submit your question using the form below.



